        "theory": "### Multi-Factor Authentication and Trust Boundaries\n#### Enforcing Identity Protection Across the Enterprise\n\nIdentity security relies on verifying trust dynamically. Since passwords are weak, Multi-Factor Authentication (MFA) requires additional validation factors.\nDefining **Trust Boundaries** is crucial: once a user crosses a trust boundary (e.g., authentication), their permissions must still be restricted under the Principle of Least Privilege (PoLP) to prevent a compromise from spilling into other zones.",
